segments.en:
Shiyin thought it was the talk of a madman and paid him no heed. The monk then pointed at Shiyin and laughed loudly, chanting four lines:
Accustomed to pampering and doting, I laugh at your folly;
The water caltrop blossom faces the melting snow in vain.
Beware after the Lantern Festival;
That will be the time when smoke vanishes and fire dies.
